Dr Bukola Saraki, one of the presidential aspirants of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, has congratulated the presidential flagbearer of the party, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar on his emergence at the presidential primary election in Abuja, weekend. The former Senate President also thanked all his friends and supporters across the nation for keying into “our vision to provide #RealSolutions and #FixNigeria!” He added that, “as we prepare for the future, I am proud that our message of #RealSolutions and deliberate leadership has resonated with millions of young Nigerians across the nation. “Now, we must all rally around all our candidates across the nation to fix our economy, curb the insecurity, and put an end to the rising cost of living.” DAILY POST recalls that the former Senate President, Saraki came third with 70 votes in the party’s presidential primary election, in which about 14 aspirants took part.